title: Old Agora
author: orikebise
pages:
#- Abandoned City History of Agora, taken from the Civcraft Wiki
Coordinates: (2491, -3068), Nether Coordinates: (312, 64, -385)
Not much is known of this small formerly abandonned city (abandonned at least since April
#- 2012) aside from being one of the former towns that were left empty after Lazuli fell. Currently a group of organized squatter's have cleaned up the mess griefers and scavengers had left and have created a squatter's pardise. The architecture
#- of Agora is primarily stone and the most prominent feature is Agora tower, the new town hall by the nether portal.
In early Janurary 2013 Agora, or as it is now known by its former residents, Old Agora, was griefed severly by an Al Kaowoni terror
#- cell, they destroyed much of the university that was being built at the time. Disheartened, most of the population made an exodus to the ruined city of Cressopolis. Here they remained private until they had cemented themselves as a city. They
#- called this city New Agora.
Now Agora, or Old Agora is inhabited by a small number of people who stayed behind. Although these people are technically ruled by government of the Agoran Republic, whose head is at New Agora, they are
#- mostly governed by self rule due to the lack of government presence.
Agora, for a time, remained a mining outpost of New Agora, but the diamond vein that it was over soon ran out and it is now rarely visited by New Agorans.
#- This is originally the work of New Agoran citizens, last modified by professor_hess, March 12, 2013, and transcribed for Minecraft book and quill by Librarian Orikebise, of the Agora State University
#- 